class:: RNNCh
summary:: Four-input recurrent neural network based on the ChowDSP ChowRNN module
categories:: UGens>Effects
related:: Guides/ChowDSPPorts

Description::

RNNCh follows the ChowDSP ChowRNN module and keeps the original `Dense(4) -> Tanh(4) -> GRU(4) -> Dense(1)` architecture. This is a compact recurrent neural network, so four input channels are linearly combined, passed through a nonlinear stage, folded into a gated recurrent-unit state, and projected back to one audio output. In DSP language it is a learnable nonlinear dynamical system: the hidden state makes the response depend on context and recent history rather than only on the current inputs.

Because the model is small and direct, RNNCh is useful as an experimental nonlinear processor as much as a finished effect. It can be driven as a compact learned system for dynamic distortion, control-to-audio mapping, or exploratory timbre design where explicit circuit interpretation is less important than stateful behavior.

definitionlist::
## in1, in2, in3, in4: || the four RNN input channels
## randomize: || rising-edge trigger that replaces the network weights using `seed`
## seed: || deterministic integer seed used on construction and on each `randomize` trigger
## reset: || rising-edge trigger that clears the GRU hidden state and DC blocker without changing the weights
::

Unlike the Rack module, this first pass does not expose JSON save/load of the weight matrices. The output-layer bias is kept at zero, and the output includes the same DC blocker as the Rack module. Rack-side jack-count makeup gain is approximated from which SC inputs are not scalar zero.

The ChowDSP-VCV repo also ships `examples/rnn.vcv`, a subtractive-voice patch built around two `ChowRNN` modules with stored weights. `RNNCh` currently does not import those saved JSON matrices, so the patch translation below mirrors the signal flow with deterministic `seed` values instead of the exact Rack models.

classmethods::

method::ar

argument::in1
Input channel 1.

argument::in2
Input channel 2.

argument::in3
Input channel 3.

argument::in4
Input channel 4.

argument::randomize
Rising-edge trigger to replace the current model weights.

argument::seed
Integer seed used for deterministic randomization.

argument::reset
Rising-edge trigger to reset the recurrent state.

argument::mul
Output multiplier.

argument::add
Output offset.


